net.fathomsoft.nova.tree.exceptionhandling

Class ExceptionNode

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.fathomsoft.nova.tree.TreeNode
      • net.fathomsoft.nova.tree.exceptionhandling.ExceptionNode

  • public class ExceptionNode
extends TreeNode
    TreeNode extension that represents an Exception instance that is to be thrown within a ThrowNode statement. 
     // Instantiate a new Exception type.
 ExceptionName varName = new ExceptionName(... optional arguments ...);
 
 // Throw the generated Exception type.
 throw varName;
    For more information on what it looks like to throw an ExceptionNode, see ThrowNode.decodeStatement(TreeNode, String, Location, boolean, boolean).

      • setType

        public void setType(java.lang.String type)
        Set the type of Exception that is being generated. If the type is unique to anything created prior to this, the id of the generated ExceptionNode will also be unique. If the Exception type has already been used before, it will use the already generated id that belongs to the ExceptionNode.
        Parameters:
        type - The name (type) of the Exception that is being generated.
